    "title": "Fatal LevelDB error: 1 missing files 069071.ldb again.",
    "body": "I get this issue no once in the last two years on different HDD's. Reindexing works fine, but what if I want to start reindexing not from 0 but from special bloks/chainstate files?\r\nFor example, now I have an error:\r\n\r\n> Fatal LevelDB error: 1 missing files 069071.ldb\r\n\r\n069071.ldb is one from the last files in chainstate. How do I start reindexing starting from a specific file? Or LevelDB organized differently internally and it only makes sense to rebuild from scratch? ",
